festival.introText: Building on the huge success of their debut, KITE plans to return with another diverse celebration of music and ideas. With previous acts including Grace Jones, Saint Etienne, Delia Smith, and Ai Weiwei, this eclectic festival is as much about widening your perspective on the world and joining in spirited debates as it is about soaking in some amazing music.

faqs.question: When is KITE Music Festival 2023?
faqs.answer: KITE Music Festival takes place on Friday 9th June - Sunday 11th June 2023.

faqs.question: How do I get to KITE Music Festival by car?
faqs.answer:
KITE will take place at Kite Festival (Blue Gate), Kirtlington Park, Akeman Street, Kidlington, OX5 3JL. It is easily accessible for the M40 with plenty of signage as you approach.

 

On-site parking is available and can either be purchased in advance or on arrival via cash. Please note you will not be allowed to park by your tent and you will not be able to stay in your vehicle overnight in the car park.

 

There will be  drop off / pick up point at the car park for those travelling via taxi.

faqs.question: KITE Music Festival ticket information
faqs.answer: For the latest KITE ticket information, please visit https://kitefestival.co.uk/tickets/.

faqs.question: Is there camping available at KITE Music Festival?
faqs.answer: Yes, there are both camping and glamping options available at KITE Music Festival as well as a live-in vehicle option. Camping tickets include your entry to the festival.

faqs.question: Accessibility information
faqs.answer: KITE provides accessible facilities. Find more information here: https://kitefestival.co.uk/accessibility/

faqs.question: Where is KITE Music Festival?
faqs.answer: KITE will take place at Kite Festival (Blue Gate), Kirtlington Park, Akeman Street, Kidlington, OX5 3JL.

faqs.question: How do I get to KITE Music Festival by train?
faqs.answer: The nearest stations to KITE or Bicester and Oxford Parkway.

faqs.question: What camping facilities are available at KITE Music Festival?
faqs.answer:
• Water Points
  • Toilets
  • Showers
  • Premium Toilets
  • Premium Showers
  • A general store with snacks, drinks and camping essentials
  • Communal fire pits

faqs.question: Does KITE Music Festival have any age restrictions?
faqs.answer: No, KITE is an all ages event with different ticket types depending on age group. Children between 0 and 5 can attend for free but you must add this to your other ticket order in order for admission.

faqs.question: How do I get to KITE Music Festival by bus?
faqs.answer: There is a bus service in operation between Bicester and Oxford, with a stop just by the entrance to KITE.

faqs.question: How do I get to KITE Music Festival by bike?
faqs.answer: There will be an area for cyclists to lock up their bikes for free at the festival entrance. Bikes are left at their owner's on risk.

faqs.question: What time does KITE Music Festival open / close?
faqs.answer:
Camping ticket holders will be able to access the campsite from 3pm on the Friday, leaving by 11am on the Monday.

 

The arena itself will open from 5pm on the Friday and 10am on the Saturday and Sunday.

 

Timings are subject to change so be sure to check https://kitefestival.co.uk/the-essentials/ nearer to the festival date.

faqs.question: Does KITE Music Festival allow re-entry?
faqs.answer:
Camping ticket holders will be allowed re-entry when showing their wristbands.

 

Other ticket holders will only be allowed a one-time entry to the festival per day.

faqs.question: What should I bring / not bring to KITE Music Festival?
faqs.answer: Find further details on what you can and can't bring to KITE here: https://kitefestival.co.uk/what-to-bring/
